# ACM (Advanced Cognitive Modelling) â€” course workspace

This repository contains small, self-contained assignments inspired by the course materials:
https://fusaroli.github.io/AdvancedCognitiveModeling2023/

Current content
- `assignment1/`: repeated Matching Pennies with a mid-game role swap; comparison of two cognitive strategies (WSLS vs k-ToM) + interpretation plot.

Reproducibility (renv)
- This repo is designed to work with **renv**.
- If a `renv.lock` exists in the repo root, run:
  - `renv::restore()`

How to run assignment 1
1. Open `ACM.Rproj` in RStudio (recommended).
2. Restore packages with renv (if you have `renv.lock`).
3. Follow `assignment1/README.md`.
